from flask import Flask, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello_world():
    data = {
        'message': 'Hello, World!',
        'number': 42
    }
    return jsonify(data)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run()
In this updated script, we've created a dictionary called data that contains two key-value pairs: 'message' and 'number'. When the / endpoint is accessed, the hello_world function returns the data dictionary in JSON format using Flask's jsonify method.

When you run this updated script and visit http://localhost:5000 in your web browser, you should see the JSON object displayed on the page, like this:

